	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b>Purify Soul and Radiant Cure</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">People are always asking about these two and if they're worth it so I figured a sort of mini-FAQ might help here<br />
<br />
<table><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>Curse</th><th>Disease</th><th>Poison</th><th>Detremental</th></tr><tr><td><b>Radiant Cure 1</b></td><td>9</td><td>9</td><td>9</td><td>1</td></tr><tr bgcolor=DDDDDD><td><b>Radiant Cure 2</b></td><td>12</td><td>12</td><td>12</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td><b>Radiant Cure 3</b></td><td>16</td><td>16</td><td>16</td><td>6</td></tr><tr bgcolor=DDDDDD><td><b>Purify Soul</b></td><td>72(36x2)</td><td>72(36x2)</td><td>72(36x2)</td><td>9(x6)</td></tr></table><br />
<br />
Radiant Cure is a 2/4/6 PoP AA. Only prerequisite is level 61/63/65 respectively. 3 min reuse<br />
<br />
Purify Soul is a cleric only class AA that requires 5 AA level 59 and Healing Gift 3. 30 min reuse (there is a 2/2/2 PoP AA that reduces reuse 10% (3 min) per level.<br />
<br />
I think the cures are pretty self explanatory. Detremental requires some explaination, however.<br />
<br />
Remove Detremental works on any detremental spell that does not have counters. The exceptions to this are Charm, Fear, Resurrection Effects and any form of Blindness. When used, RD attempts to remove any spells that are classified as detremental present on you. If RD fails to remove an effect it reduces its duration by half. This was confirmed directly by Rich Waters of SOE.<br />
<br />
The numbers in the chart are the level of RD each spell has. The higher the level of RD the more likely it is to remove a given effect. Purify Soul has 6 of the RD9 effects inside.<br />
<br />
FAQs<br />
<br />
<b>How do I know if an effect on me can only be cured by RC/PS?</b><br />
Check out <a href="http://lucy.fnord.net" target="_blank">Lucy</a> and search for that effect. If it has "Increase XXXX Counter by Y" in it then you can cure it by just casting the appropriate cure (remember, RC and PS have all cures in them). If there are no counters listed then it can only be removed by RC/PS.<br />
Examples:<br />
<a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=4288&source=Live" target="_blank">Can be removed by spells</a><br />
<a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=242&source=Live" target="_blank">Can only be removed by RC/PS</a><br />
*NOTE* You can dispell a number of negative effects (but some are difficult to remove with dispell) but RC and PS are "magic bullets" that will leave your good buffs alone. Thanks to all who noted this.<br />
<br />
<b>I cast RC but it didn't remove the spell. What's wrong?</b><br />
Nothing. Remember, RC has a weaker version of RD so it may not work very often on some higher end spells (especially if you only have RC 1 or 2) but it will still reduce the duration by half. Incidentally, I have never seen PS fail to remove a spell.<br />
<br />
<b>Is buying RC 2 and/or 3 worth the AAs?</b><br />
Maybe. If you're in the end game you will encounter more counterless AE spells. RC2 and 3 are definitely worth the AA investment then. Otherwise RC1 does a decent enough job against most AEs.<br />
<br />
<b>Is PS (with HG3) worth the investment?</b><br />
It really depends on the circumstances in the above question. If you're constantly dealing with AE spells you can't cure with spells then PS is definitely worth the investment. As I said, I have not found any spell that PS would not cure and that is invaluable against some AE spells.</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
